---

<Layout title={post.title} description={post.description}>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(articleSchema)} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(localBusinessSchema)} />

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-8 pt-16 pb-24">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <span class="inline-block bg-primary/5 border border-primary/20 text-primary px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-label font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">
        {post.category}
      </span>
      <p class="text-secondary font-body text-sm mb-4">{post.date}</p>
      <h1 class="font-headline text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tighter text-on-surface mb-4">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        Choosing between small and large bubble wrap sizes is confusing for many Malaysian online sellers. This guide explains the differences, cost implications, and best applications for each bubble size.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">
        Understanding Bubble Wrap Sizes
      </h2>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Bubble wrap is sized by the diameter of its air bubbles. The two most common sizes in Malaysia are:
      </p>
      <ul class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-3 list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong>Small bubble wrap (10mm):</strong> Tightly-packed bubbles, 10 millimeters in diameter. Suitable for light items and maximum cushioning density per unit area.</li>
        <li><strong>Large bubble wrap (25mm):</strong> Bigger bubbles, 25 millimeters in diameter. Provides more cushioning per wrap but uses less material per item.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Less common are micro bubble (6mm) for jewelry and premium items, and jumbo bubble (50mm) for heavy furniture and industrial applications.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">
        Small Bubble Wrap (10mm): Best Uses and Advantages
      </h2>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
        What Small Bubble Excels At
      </h3>
      <ul class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>Electronics (phones, tablets, computers, accessories)</li>
        <li>Fragile ceramics, glassware, and porcelain</li>
        <li>Jewelry and small luxury items</li>
        <li>Items with detailed surfaces vulnerable to denting</li>
        <li>Cosmetics and beauty products</li>
        <li>Books and delicate documents</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
        Advantages of Small Bubble
      </h3>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">
        The tightly-packed structure provides uniform, dense protection. No gaps between bubbles means no pressure points on fragile items. This is ideal for items where even small dents or scratches reduce value significantly (phones, laptops, gaming consoles).
      </p>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        Small bubble also wraps more neatly around products, creating a professional appearance. For premium unboxing experiences, small bubble looks more refined than large bubble.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
        Cost of Small Bubble
      </h3>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        RM 0.80-1.20 per square meter. For a typical item requiring 2 wraps, expect RM 0.15-0.25 material cost per item.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">
        Large Bubble Wrap (25mm): Best Uses and Advantages
      </h2>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
        What Large Bubble Excels At
      </h3>
      <ul class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>Furniture and upholstered items</li>
        <li>Larger electronics (TVs, monitors, speakers)</li>
        <li>Appliances and heavy items</li>
        <li>Outdoor gear and sporting equipment</li>
        <li>Items that can tolerate occasional pressure points</li>
        <li>Situations where material cost is paramount</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
        Advantages of Large Bubble
      </h3>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Each layer of large bubble provides 2.5x more cushioning per wrap than small bubble. For heavy items that can tolerate some impact, large bubble is more efficient. You achieve equivalent protection with half the material, reducing both material cost and box dimensions.
      </p>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        Large bubble wraps faster, reducing labor time. For high-volume packaging (100+ items daily), this speed advantage translates to significant operational savings.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
        Cost of Large Bubble
      </h3>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        RM 1.00-1.50 per square meter. While slightly higher per sqm, you use significantly less, often making total cost per item comparable to or cheaper than small bubble.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">
        Direct Comparison: Small vs Large Bubble Wrap
      </h2>

      <div class="bg-surface-variant/50 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-2xl p-6 my-8">
        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-0 mb-4">
          Small vs Large Bubble Wrap Comparison
        </h3>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full font-body text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-2 font-bold">Attribute</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-2 font-bold">Small Bubble (10mm)</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-2 font-bold">Large Bubble (25mm)</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
                <td class="py-3 px-2 font-bold">Bubble Diameter</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">10mm</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">25mm</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
                <td class="py-3 px-2 font-bold">Cushioning per Wrap</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">Standard</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">2.5x more</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
                <td class="py-3 px-2 font-bold">Cost per sqm</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">RM 0.80-1.20</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">RM 1.00-1.50</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
                <td class="py-3 px-2 font-bold">Material per Item (2 wraps)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">RM 0.15-0.25</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">RM 0.10-0.15</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
                <td class="py-3 px-2 font-bold">Wraps Needed (Phone)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">2-3 wraps</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">1-2 wraps</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
                <td class="py-3 px-2 font-bold">Wraps Needed (Furniture)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">3-4 wraps</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">2 wraps</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
                <td class="py-3 px-2 font-bold">Appearance</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">Premium, refined</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">Functional, economical</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
                <td class="py-3 px-2 font-bold">Packing Speed</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">Slower (more wraps)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">Faster (fewer wraps)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 px-2 font-bold">Best For</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">Electronics, luxury items</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-2">Furniture, heavy items</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">
        Item-by-Item Bubble Wrap Size Guide
      </h2>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
        Electronics & Appliances
      </h3>
      <ul class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong>Phones, tablets, cameras:</strong> Small bubble, 2 wraps</li>
        <li><strong>Laptops, monitors:</strong> Large bubble, 2 wraps or small bubble, 3 wraps</li>
        <li><strong>TVs:</strong> Large bubble, 2-3 wraps + honeycomb cardboard reinforcement</li>
        <li><strong>Speakers, headphones:</strong> Small bubble, 1-2 wraps</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
        Fragile Items
      </h3>
      <ul class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong>Glassware, dishes:</strong> Small bubble, 2-3 wraps</li>
        <li><strong>Ceramic vases:</strong> Small bubble, 2 wraps</li>
        <li><strong>Artwork, paintings:</strong> Small bubble, 2 wraps + cardboard backing</li>
        <li><strong>Mirrors:</strong> Small bubble, 2 wraps + honeycomb cardboard edge protection</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
        Clothing & Soft Items
      </h3>
      <ul class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong>Shoes, bags, accessories:</strong> Large bubble, 1 wrap or small bubble, 1-2 wraps</li>
        <li><strong>Clothing:</strong> Kraft paper crumple (bubble usually unnecessary)</li>
        <li><strong>Books:</strong> Large bubble, 1 wrap</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
        Furniture & Large Items
      </h3>
      <ul class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong>Sofas, chairs:</strong> Large bubble, multiple wraps + honeycomb corners</li>
        <li><strong>Tables, shelves:</strong> Large bubble, 2-3 wraps</li>
        <li><strong>Bedroom furniture:</strong> Large bubble, 2 wraps + honeycomb protection</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">
        Cost Analysis: Which Size Saves Money?
      </h2>

      <div class="bg-surface-variant/50 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-2xl p-6 my-8">
        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-0 mb-4">
          Monthly Bubble Wrap Cost: 1,000 Items Example
        </h3>
        <ul class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-2 list-none">
          <li><strong>Small bubble (2 wraps per item):</strong> 1,000 items × 2 wraps × RM 0.20 = RM 400/month</li>
          <li><strong>Large bubble (1 wrap per item):</strong> 1,000 items × 1 wrap × RM 0.12 = RM 120/month</li>
          <li className="border-t border-outline-variant/20 pt-2 mt-2"><strong>Monthly savings with large bubble:</strong> RM 280</li>
          <li><strong>Annual savings:</strong> RM 3,360</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="font-body text-label text-sm text-secondary mt-4">
          Note: This assumes both protect items equally well. If small bubble prevents 5% more damage claims, cost-benefit favors small bubble for electronics.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">
        Buying Bubble Wrap in Bulk From Quinocycle
      </h2>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Quinocycle supplies both small and large bubble wrap in bulk rolls, with flexible minimum orders and competitive wholesale pricing.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
        Bulk Pricing & Availability
      </h3>
      <ul class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong>Minimum order:</strong> RM 1,000 (typically 4-6 rolls depending on size)</li>
        <li><strong>Standard roll size:</strong> 100m × 60cm (300 sqm per roll)</li>
        <li><strong>Volume discounts:</strong> Apply for orders above RM 5,000</li>
        <li><strong>Delivery:</strong> Same-day collection in Balakong, next-day delivery elsewhere in Malaysia</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-surface-variant/50 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-2xl p-6">
        <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <strong>Ready to stock the right bubble wrap size for your products?</strong> Quinocycle offers both small and large bubble in bulk with expert guidance on sizing for your items.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 mt-6">
          <a href={WA_LINK} target="_blank" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center bg-primary text-on-primary font-label font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest px-6 py-3 rounded-full hover:bg-primary/90 transition-colors">
            Chat on WhatsApp
          </a>
          <a href="mailto:quinocycle@gmail.com" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center bg-surface-variant text-on-surface border border-outline-variant/20 font-label font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest px-6 py-3 rounded-full hover:bg-surface-variant/80 transition-colors">
            Email Us
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 mt-6">
        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer group">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface text-lg flex justify-between items-center">
            What is the difference between small and large bubble wrap?
            <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Small bubble wrap (10mm) has tightly-packed bubbles for lightweight, delicate items. Large bubble wrap (25mm) has bigger bubbles providing more cushioning for heavier items and rough handling. Small bubble costs 20-30% less per sqm but offers less protection per layer.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer group">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface text-lg flex justify-between items-center">
            Which bubble wrap size is best for electronics?
            <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mt-4">
            For electronics, small bubble wrap (10mm) is usually sufficient for phones, tablets, and small electronics. Larger electronics (TVs, monitors) benefit from large bubble wrap (25mm) or double-wrapping with small bubble. Consider the fragility of components inside.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer group">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface text-lg flex justify-between items-center">
            How much bubble wrap do I need per item?
            <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mt-4">
            For small items, 1-2 wraps of small bubble is sufficient. For medium items (shoes, clothing), 2-3 wraps. For fragile items, wrap 2-3 times regardless of size. Large bubble wrap provides equivalent protection with fewer wraps, saving material and reducing box size.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer group">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface text-lg flex justify-between items-center">
            What is the cost difference between bubble wrap sizes?
            <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Small bubble wrap: RM 0.80-1.20 per sqm. Large bubble wrap: RM 1.00-1.50 per sqm. While large bubble costs slightly more per sqm, you use less of it per item, often making total cost comparable or lower than small bubble.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer group">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface text-lg flex justify-between items-center">
            Can I buy bubble wrap in bulk from Quinocycle?
            <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
