    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">
        Conclusion: The Right Size for Your Products
      </h2>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Choosing between small and large bubble wrap depends entirely on what you're shipping. Small bubble excels for electronics and delicate items where surface protection matters. Large bubble wins for furniture, heavy items, and cost-conscious operations where material efficiency matters most.
      </p>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        The smartest approach is to stock both sizes and deploy each strategically. Your packaging costs will drop, your products will arrive in better condition, and your customers will appreciate the careful attention to protection.
      </p>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed">
